  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and cut them into large, bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until they're fork-tender</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain and return the cooked&nbsp;<strong>potatoes</strong> to the pot to steam dry&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>chicken thigh fillets</strong> into large pieces</p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chicken</strong>&nbsp;with a generous pinch of both<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 6 min, or until golden, turning once half way&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the<strong>&nbsp;golden chicken</strong> to a plate and set aside, keeping the pan</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>smoked streaky</strong>&nbsp;<strong>bacon</strong> into small, bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel the<strong> shallots</strong> and cut them into quarters</p>\r\n<p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped bacon</strong> and cook for 2 min or until it's beginning to crisp</p>\r\n<p>Once crispy, add the<strong>&nbsp;quartered shallot</strong>&nbsp;and<strong> baby chestnut mushrooms</strong> and cook for 4 min further, or until everything's beginning to caramelise and brown&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the<strong> bacon</strong>, <strong>shallot</strong> and <strong>mushroom</strong> to a plate, keeping the pan</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-4-x400.jpg",
