          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/960.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a large knob of<strong> butter</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once melted, add the<strong>&nbsp;sliced leek</strong> and<strong> bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span></strong>&nbsp;with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 3 min or until they're beginning to soften, then add the&nbsp;<strong>sliced garlic </strong>and<strong>&nbsp;</strong>cook for a further 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Stir 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong>&nbsp;into the <strong>softened</strong>&nbsp;<strong>leek</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>",
